            "text": "ROOT",
            "relation": "null"
        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "The cell intrinsic innate immune responses provide a first line of defense against viral infection ,",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "and often function",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "by targeting cellular pathways",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "usurped by the virus during infection . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "In particular , many viruses manipulate cellular lipids",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "to form complex structures",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "required for viral replication ,",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "many of which are dependent on de novo fatty acid synthesis . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "We found",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "that the energy regulator AMPK ,",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "which potently inhibits fatty acid synthesis ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "restricts infection of the Bunyavirus , Rift Valley Fever Virus ( RVFV ) , an important re - emerging arthropod - borne human pathogen",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "for which there are no effective vaccines or therapeutics . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "We show restriction of RVFV both by AMPK and its upstream activator LKB1 ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "indicating an antiviral role for this signaling pathway . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "Furthermore , we found",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "that AMPK is activated during RVFV infection ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "leading to the phosphorylation and inhibition of acetyl - CoA carboxylase , the first rate - limiting enzyme in fatty acid synthesis . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 19,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "Activating AMPK pharmacologically both restricted infection",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 20,
            "parent": 19,
            "text": "and reduced lipid levels . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 21,
            "parent": 19,
            "text": "This restriction could be bypassed by treatment with the fatty acid palmitate ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 22,
            "parent": 23,
            "text": "demonstrating",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 23,
            "parent": 21,
            "text": "that AMPK restricts RVFV infection through its inhibition of fatty acid biosynthesis . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 24,
            "parent": 25,
            "text": "Lastly , we found",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 25,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "that this pathway plays a broad role in antiviral defense",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 26,
            "parent": 25,
            "text": "since additional viruses from disparate families were also restricted by AMPK and LKB1 . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 27,
            "parent": 25,
            "text": "Therefore , AMPK is an important component of the cell intrinsic immune response",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 28,
            "parent": 27,
            "text": "that restricts infection through a novel mechanism",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 29,
            "parent": 28,
            "text": "involving the inhibition of fatty acid metabolism . <S> <P>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        }
    ]
}